AN ACT IMPLEMENTING THE RECOMMENDATIONS OF THE TASK
FORCE TO SUPPORT PROMISE PROGRAMS IN THE STATE.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General
Assembly convened:
1 Section 1. (NEW) (Effective July 1, 2026) (a) As used in this section,
2 "promise program" means a scholarship program that provides a
3 scholarship in conjunction with services and resources, including, but
4 not limited to, mentoring, peer support networks and internships, to
5 scholarship recipients to ensure the postsecondary academic success of
6 such recipients.
7 (b) (1) Not later than September 1, 2026, and annually thereafter, the
8 Office of Higher Education shall provide a grant to each promise
9 program in the state that was established during or prior to the previous
10 fiscal year. Such grant shall be in an amount equal to three thousand
11 dollars per student enrolled in such promise program.
12 (2) Not later than July 1, 2027, and annually thereafter, each promise
